sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K197037
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a cell surface display device that will enable engineered cells to bind silver via the fusion of a silver binding peptide to the surface of E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jennifer Brophy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M10093
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Composite part with Arabinose promoter, ribosome binding site, prepro periplasmic targetting sequence, and a streptavidin-binding tag in frame with the BglBricks scar.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K197023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The Silver Binding peptide binds and reduces silver for biomineralization purposes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gabriela Guzman Lopez Aguado
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Wobble Odvs002F/Odvs002R to make M10023 (Bdvs002) (67 bp, EcoRI/BamHI) Sub into pBca9495AK-Bca1144#5 (EcoRI/BamHI, 3171+910, L) Product is pBca9495AK-M10023 {<AG4>} (3222bp) ---- Odvs002F Forward construction of AG4 basic part ccataGAATTCATGAGATCTAACCCGTCTTCTCTGTTCCGTTACCTGCC Odvs002R Reverse construction of AG4 basic part ctgatGGATCCGTCAGACGGCAGGTAACGGAACAGAGAAGACGG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K197009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A 12-stranded beta barrel. Autotransporters are proteins that form a pore in the outermembrane and and pull their N terminus through this pore in order to expose it to the extracellular space. N-terminal fusions of proteins to this part may permit the cell surface display of the fused protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gabriela Guzman Lopez Aguado

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
